b'' b'droplet vol no part b'' b'd r o p l e t' b"from the vast ocean of the miraculous qur'an" b'' b'translations from the arabic and turkish writings of' b'bediuzzaman said nursi, the risale-i noor' b'' b'vol no part b'------------------------------------------------------------------' b'nineteenth letter' b'' b"mu'jizat-i ahmediye risalesi" b'a treatise on the miracles of muhammed saw, part b'' b'(continued from droplet vol no part b'' b'third sign: the miracles of muhammad (saw)' b'are extremely varied. because his messengership is' b'universal, he has been distinguished by miracles that' b'relate to almost all species of creation.' b'just as the supreme aide of a renowned ruler, arriving' b'with many gifts in a city where various people live, will be' b'welcomed by a representative of each people who' b'acclaims him and bids him welcome in his own language' b'so, too, when the supreme messenger of the monarch of' b'pre- and post-eternity (ezel and ebed sultani) honored the' b'universe by coming as an envoy to the inhabitants of the' b'earth, and brought with him the light of truth and spiritual' b'gifts sent by the creator of the universe and derived from' b'the realities of the whole universe, each species of' b'creation -from water, rocks, trees, animals and human' b'beings to the moon, sun and stars- welcomed him and' b'acclaimed his prophethood, each in its own language, and' b'each bearing one of his miracles.' b'now it would require a voluminous work to mention all' b'his miracles. as the punctilious scholars have written' b'many volumes concerning the proofs of his prophethood,' b'here we will briefly point out only the general category' b'into which fall fhe miracles that are definite and accepted' b'as accurate reports.' b'the evidences of the prophethood of muhammad' b'(saw) fall into two main categories:' b'' b'the first is called irhasat and includes the paranormal' b'events that happened at the time of his birth, or before his' b'declaration of prophethood.' b'' b'the second group pertains to all the remaining evidences' b'of the prophethood, and contains two subdivisions:' b'' b'1) those wonders that were manifested after' b'his departure from this world in order to confirm his' b'prophethood, and' b'2) those that he exhibited during the era' b'of his prophethood. the latter has also two parts:' b'2.1) the evidences of his prophethood that became manifest' b'in his own personality, his inner and outer being, his moral' b'conduct and perfection, and' b'2.2) the miracles that: related to substantial matters.' b'the last part again has two branches:' b"2.2.1) those concerning the qur'an and spirituality, and" b'2.2.2) those relating to matter and creation. this last' b'branch is again divided into two categories:' b'2.2.2.1) the first involves the paranormal happenings' b'that occured during his mission either to break the' b'stubbornness of the unbelievers, or to augment the' b'faith of the belivers. this category has twenty different' b'sorts, such as the splitting of the moon, the flowing of' b'water from the fingers, the satisfying of large numbers with' b'a little food, and the speaking of trees, rocks and animals' b'each of these sons has also many instances, and thus' b'has, in meaning, the strength of confirmation by' b'consensus.' b'2.2.2.2) as for the second category, this' b'includes events lying in the future that occured as he had' b"predicted upon allah (swt)'s instructions. now starting" b'from the last category, we will summarize a list of them.(1)' b'' b'(1) unfonunately, i could not write as i had intended' b'without choice, i wrote as my head dictated, and i could' b'not completely conform to the order of this classification.' b'' b'-----------------------------------------------------------------' b'to be continued allah willing.' b'irfan alan, a servant of islam.' b'' 